body:
My opinion: This is a classic TOCTOU (Time-Of-Check-To-Time-Of-Use) pattern that can cause race conditions. The issue is valid but the impact is low because events are processed sequentially from a single goroutine via channels in both `receiveCommit()` and `receiveCommitRequest()`
To fix it we would change to a single `Lock()` instead of `RLock()`/`RUnlock()`/`Lock()` pattern
@DarkKnight3074
